.player-box
    | Ready Player 
    span.player {{currentPlayer.name}}
    | .
  .board
    .row1
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(1,1)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(1,1)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(1,2)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(1,2)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(1,3)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(1,3)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(1,4)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(1,4)')
    .row2
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(2,1)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(2,1)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(2,2)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(2,2)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(2,3)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(2,3)')
      |     
      span.peg(class='{{pegStyle(2,4)}}', ng-click='pegClicked(2,4)')
  .message-box(ng-show='messageKey || game.gameOver')
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'games.post.error'")
      | Oh snap! Something went wrong creating your game. 
      a.alert-link(ng-click='newGame()', href='javascript:void(0)') Try again?
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'pegs.notSelected.error'")
      | You have to select a peg in order to move a peg.
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'pegs.user.error'")
      | {{message}}
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'games.notFound.error'")
      | Woops! That game doesn&apos;t exist any more. Would you like to create a 
      a.alert-link(ng-click='newGame()', href='javascript:void(0)') new game?
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'pegs.conflict.error'")
      | You can&apos;t move a different peg than what is selected.
    span.warning(ng-show="messageKey == 'pegs.put.error'")
      | Gremlins got into your game. They may have broken your game permanently but try taking another turn just in case this is a false alarm.
    span.info(ng-show='game.gameOver && !messageKey')
      | Game Over! 
      a.alert-link(ng-click='newGame()', href='javascript:void(0)') Try again?
  .message-box(ng-hide='messageKey || game.gameOver')
    | To take your turn, select a peg and then select a vacant (white) space.
